  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Observation of $\nu \mu \to \nu \tau$ oscillations in the CNGS beam with the OPERA experiment</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2015-05-29</subfield>
    <subfield code="t">published</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="300" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">8</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="9">EDP Sciences</subfield>
    <subfield code="a">The OPERA long-baseline neutrino experiment was exposed to the CNGS nu_mu beam from 2008 to 2012, collecting 19505 interactions in the target. The evidence for oscillated nu_tau appearance, based on the observation of three nu_tau candidate events, has been previously reported. A fourth candidate event has been recently found in an extended data sample, corresponding to about 89% of the final statistics. The absence of a signal from nu_mu -> nu_tau oscillations is currently excluded at 4.2sigma. The status of the analysis is described in detail with special emphasis on the procedures applied for the selection of signal candidate events and the assessment of efficiencies and background. The fourth nu_tau candidate event is presented and the significance of the observation is discussed.</subfield>
  </datafield>
